#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation from the source tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Get the sources Luke!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You can download the last official release from [the "
"forge](http://forge.fusioninventory.org/projects/fusioninventory-agent/files)  "
"or directly from [the "
"CPAN](https://metacpan.org/release/FusionInventory-Agent)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Tarball with a **rc** or **beta** version suffix are developpement release "
"not ready for production."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "It's also possible to get snapshot from Github:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "[Agent 2.2.x](https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent/tarball/2.2.x)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "[Agent 2.3.x](https://github.com/fusinv/fusioninventory-agent/tarball/2.3.x)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "agent from sources"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We strongly recommand the use of __GNU tar__ because some file path lenght "
"are greater than 100 caracters. Some tar version will silently ignore those "
"files like for example on HP-UX."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "First, you need to extract the source and run the Makefile.PL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    tar xfz FusionInventory-Agent-2.2.5.tar.gz\n"
"    cd FusionInventory-Agent-2.2.5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Makefile.PL will ensure all the required dependencies are available and "
"prepare the build tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    perl Makefile.PL\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"At this point, you will probably have some missing required modules. The "
"best tool to resolve the situation is "
"[cpanm](https://raw.github.com/miyagawa/cpanminus/master/cpanm). Just run:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    cpanm .\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You can use the _--notest_ flag if you are brave and want to skip the "
"test-suite execution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You may also need to install some [[system specific "
"dependencies|documentation/agent/system_dep]]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Once this is done, run once again:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    perl Makefile.Pl\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This time the execution should success and you can finish the "
"installation. Here again we recommand GNU make (gmake):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    make\n"
"    make install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Change the installation directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If you don't want to use the default directory (/usr/local), you can use the "
"PREFIX parameter during the Makefile.PL step:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    perl Makefile.PL PREFIX=/opt/fusioninventory\n"
"    make\n"
"    make test\n"
"    make install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "plugins installation from source"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The plugin installation follow the same process:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    tar xfz FusionInventory-Agent-Task-Foo-0.1.2.tar.gz\n"
"    cd FusionInventory-Agent-Task-Foo-0.1.2\n"
"    cpanm .\n"
"    perl Makefile.PL\n"
"    make install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Agent will read it's configuration from /etc/fusioninventory/agent.cfg. You "
"need at least a `server` line:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    server = http://server.domain.com/glpi/plugins/fusioninventory/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "crontab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You can use the [crontab](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron) to launch the "
"agent. The agent will need a correctly initialized $PATH environment "
"variable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "This is an example of an /etc/crontab entry:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin\n"
"    17 *    * * *   root   fusioninventory-agent\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "SSL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"SSL communication are based on "
"[IO::Socket::SSL](https://metacpan.org/module/IO::Socket::SSL). You build it "
"you will need openssl header files and a C compiler."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If you don't want to use SSL, you can avoid keep this dependency "
"uninstalled.  The agent will disable SSL by itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Test-suite"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"FusionInventory components come with a test-suite. You can run it after the "
"`perl Makefile.PL` with this command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    make test\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The test-suites require some additional dependencies like Test::More."
msgstr ""
